  "body": "prysm should take the consensus time from the peers as an alternative to the hosts own time reference. \n\nin the event the hosts time significant deviates from that of the beaconchain then a new time consensus algo kicks in to determine which is right.\n\nat the same time minor deltas should probably yield to the local hosts time material ones should be viewed as an external attack. when smoothed out, the eth2 network should end up being almost a unilateral universal source of time. \n\n@nisdas",
